timelineItems.name: Steve Brisendine
timelineItems.text: Even with Royals opening ALCS, full house at Sporting Park. Well done.

timelineItems.comment: Lineups are announced and players are warming up.
Offside, Sporting Kansas City. Jacob Peterson tries a through ball, but Paulo Nagamura is caught offside.

timelineItems.name: Lefty Gauge Webster
timelineItems.text: My goodness what a goal by @gzusi #SportingKC

timelineItems.name: James Patrick Gordon
timelineItems.text: SJ doesn't even get mad anymore. I guess there's no point. #cf97

timelineItems.name: Haley Weatherford
timelineItems.text: ZUSI YOU ARE THE MAN. WHAT DID I TELL YOU. TAKE MORE SHOTS. TAKE. MORE. SHOTS. #SKCvCHI #beautiful

timelineItems.name: Stacey
timelineItems.text: WHATEVER YOURE DOING KEEP DOING IT- THIS IS NOT A DRILL!! KEEP IT UP ROYALS AND SKC!! #Royals #IBelieveThatWeWillWin #SKCvCHI

timelineItems.name: Jared Coffman
timelineItems.text: At first watch that was a spectacular goal. After the replay, that was a world class goal #SportingKC #SKCvCHI

timelineItems.comment: Attempt missed. Sanna Nyassi (Chicago Fire) left footed shot from outside the box is just a bit too high.

timelineItems.name: Shane Murray
timelineItems.text: A goal worthy of winning any game. What a strike by @gzusi! Can the Fire claim a late equalizer? Wouldn't be unlike them. #cf97 #SKCvCHI

timelineItems.name: Adam Overberg
timelineItems.text: Sean Johnson's been great all night, it was going to take something special to beat him. Zusi more than up to the task #SKCvCHI

timelineItems.name: Lauren Pasquith
timelineItems.text: Celebratory Dom and Zusi hug! GOAL SKC! #SportingKC #SKC #CapFedSKCMoments

timelineItems.comment: Delay over. They are ready to continue.
Delay in match Igor Julião (Sporting Kansas City) because of an injury.

timelineItems.name: Troy Pike
timelineItems.text: Goal!!! #SportingKC #PutOutTheFire

timelineItems.name: Chow
timelineItems.text: I believe that we will tie. #cf97

timelineItems.comment: Foul by Sanna Nyassi (Chicago Fire).
Igor Julião (Sporting Kansas City) wins a free kick on the right wing.

timelineItems.desc: Quincy Amarikwa (Chicago Fire) is shown the yellow card for a bad foul.
timelineItems.title: YELLOW CARD: Quincy Amarikwa sees the book for a late foul

timelineItems.comment: Foul by Quincy Amarikwa (Chicago Fire).
Mikey Lopez (Sporting Kansas City) wins a free kick in the defensive half.

timelineItems.text:

timelineItems.comment: Foul by Graham Zusi (Sporting Kansas City).
Sanna Nyassi (Chicago Fire) wins a free kick in the defensive half.

timelineItems.name: Jr Ortiz ⚽️⚽️⚽️
timelineItems.text: A Chivas USA reject has played more minutes than a #USMNTU23 starter. Think about that #cf97

timelineItems.name: Ramsey_19
timelineItems.text: Yay. Fondy on to save the day. #cf97 #bigsigning #whoishe

timelineItems.name: Morgan Snell
timelineItems.text: Sporting Park is buzzing tonight! #skc #kcpride

timelineItems.name: Kurtis Larson
timelineItems.text: Do 18 regular season draws mean you're verging on greatness, or close to disastrous? #CF97

timelineItems.comment: Attempt blocked. Sanna Nyassi (Chicago Fire) right footed shot from the left side of the box is blocked.

timelineItems.name: Kyle Rohde
timelineItems.text: Also loving the @SonsofAnarchy style banner at @SportingPark don't you @sutterink? #SportingKC http://t.co/GuGk6voyGC

timelineItems.desc: Goal!  Sporting Kansas City 2, Chicago Fire 0. Dominic Dwyer (Sporting Kansas City) header from the center of the box to the bottom right corner.
timelineItems.title: GOAL: Dom Dwyer header seals a playoff spot for SKC

timelineItems.comment: Attempt saved. Matthew Fondy (Chicago Fire) right footed shot from the centre of the box is saved in the centre of the goal.

timelineItems.name: Jody Strauch
timelineItems.text: I *heart* Andy. #SKC

timelineItems.name: Brian Sandalow
timelineItems.text: Oh, Matt Fondy. #cf97

timelineItems.name: il Generale USA
timelineItems.text: WE CAN STILL GET 20 DRAWS. DO NOT GIVE UP HOPE. #CF97

timelineItems.name: Dave Flynt
timelineItems.text: Atta boy Dwyer. Back to the playoffs for #SKC

timelineItems.name: J.B. Bauersfeld
timelineItems.text: Re-Dom-tion for that missed PK. #SportingKC

timelineItems.name: James Patrick Gordon
timelineItems.text: Yup. Precisely what we deserve. #cf97

timelineItems.name: Ryan Brister
timelineItems.text: Despite tonight's win, I wouldn't exactly fear #SKC in the playoffs.

timelineItems.name: Laine Saunders
timelineItems.text: Playoff bound. #SKC

timelineItems.comment: Second Half ends, Sporting Kansas City 2, Chicago Fire 0.
